The paper deals with the performance of multi-cell massive MIMO systems, which involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), multimedia (cs.MM), and communication (cs.COM). The use of time-division duplex protocol and maximum ratio combining (MRC) at the base stations (BSs) also suggests a focus on wireless communication and networking, which further supports the likelihood of cs.NI and cs.COM as relevant sub-categories.
